It's fine. It's just once.

608
00:27:35,687 --> 00:27:38,023
If you don't feel like going to
the hospital,

609
00:27:38,523 --> 00:27:41,226
we can go somewhere else. I'll join you.

610
00:27:42,694 --> 00:27:44,229
Like where?

611
00:27:44,295 --> 00:27:45,864
Anywhere you want.

612
00:27:46,364 --> 00:27:48,333
The movies, or Disneyland.

613
00:27:50,335 --> 00:27:53,071
We're not going to Disneyland right now.

614
00:27:53,138 --> 00:27:54,606
Then, we could go bowling.

615
00:28:16,961 --> 00:28:18,196
With Jadwiga,

616
00:28:19,564 --> 00:28:20,865
we added the ears, right?

617
00:28:22,067 --> 00:28:23,034
Yeah.

618
00:28:23,601 --> 00:28:25,437
Wouldn't it be cool if those ears

619
00:28:26,971 --> 00:28:28,239
can get bigger so she can fly?

620
00:28:28,807 --> 00:28:30,442
That's a great idea!

621
00:28:48,159 --> 00:28:49,094
Ow.

622
00:29:06,177 --> 00:29:07,145
No way.

623
00:29:14,786 --> 00:29:15,754
Ouch.

624
00:29:17,088 --> 00:29:18,623
Not really.

625
00:29:25,430 --> 00:29:26,464
Killing time.

626
00:29:28,399 --> 00:29:29,234
What?

627
00:29:30,168 --> 00:29:32,103
This is what killing time is, right?

628
00:29:34,339 --> 00:29:36,074
When I didn't want to go home,

629
00:29:37,876 --> 00:29:39,077
when I was little,

630
00:29:39,677 --> 00:29:41,980
I was always killing time by myself,
like this.

631
00:29:45,116 --> 00:29:46,618
Me too.

632
00:29:50,021 --> 00:29:51,122
Now, it's the two of us.

633
00:29:53,358 --> 00:29:54,192
Yeah.

634
00:29:57,529 --> 00:29:58,763
The other day, Hikaru…

635
00:29:58,830 --> 00:30:00,765
Sora's college friend.

636
00:30:00,832 --> 00:30:02,667
Hikaru came, and asked you

637
00:30:02,734 --> 00:30:05,203
about Aoi's blood type, right?

638
00:30:05,270 --> 00:30:07,739
-Yeah.
-That time he did.

639
00:30:07,806 --> 00:30:09,908
I exchanged phone numbers with him.

640
00:30:09,974 --> 00:30:12,677
-Then let's call and explain…
-Wait a minute.

641
00:30:12,744 --> 00:30:15,880
You're Type O. Sora's type AB.
Does Sora know this?

642
00:30:15,947 --> 00:30:16,781
Yeah.

643
00:30:17,415 --> 00:30:20,185
I knew it since she was three-months-old.

644
00:30:20,685 --> 00:30:22,453
So I tried to prevent her

645
00:30:22,520 --> 00:30:24,823
from doing blood type tests, but…

646
00:30:25,356 --> 00:30:28,159
But then, when she was a freshman
in high school,

647
00:30:28,226 --> 00:30:29,594
maybe it was eighth grade,

648
00:30:29,661 --> 00:30:32,430
she went to a blood drive with a friend.

649
00:30:32,931 --> 00:30:35,333
She said, "Mom, I'm Type AB."

650
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:39,003
How did she find out you're Type O?

651
00:30:39,070 --> 00:30:41,606
-From magazine interview profile pages.
-Oh…

652
00:30:42,607 --> 00:30:43,474
And then?

653
00:30:44,008 --> 00:30:45,577
Oh, right.

654
00:30:45,643 --> 00:30:47,679
But she didn't realize that a Type O mom

655
00:30:47,745 --> 00:30:49,380
-can't have a Type AB child.
-I see.

656
00:30:50,748 --> 00:30:52,684
So I just left it like that!

657
00:30:52,750 --> 00:30:54,252
You just left it, huh?

658
00:30:54,319 --> 00:30:56,888
I knew a day like this would come one day,

659
00:30:56,955 --> 00:30:58,289
but,

660
00:30:58,356 --> 00:31:00,291
I thought maybe

661
00:31:00,358 --> 00:31:01,826
I could play dumb.

662
00:31:03,628 --> 00:31:04,963
Shunichiro.

663
00:31:05,663 --> 00:31:07,298
Do you think I have to

664
00:31:07,365 --> 00:31:09,300
tell her the truth?

665
00:31:09,367 --> 00:31:10,602
-Hm?
-Wait, Aoi.

666
00:31:11,436 --> 00:31:13,104
We're way past that stage.

667
00:31:14,072 --> 00:31:17,308
Hikaru came to our place to ask about

668
00:31:17,375 --> 00:31:20,078
you and Sora's blood types,

669
00:31:20,144 --> 00:31:22,146
and your maternity handbook position
had shifted, right?

670
00:31:22,647 --> 00:31:25,884
Sora already saw what your blood type was.

671
00:31:26,851 --> 00:31:28,987
Please fill in the patient form.

672
00:31:29,053 --> 00:31:29,954
Yes.

673
00:31:32,290 --> 00:31:33,358
INCOMING CALL

674
00:31:35,093 --> 00:31:36,628
TEST RESULT DESK

675
00:31:36,694 --> 00:31:37,562
Yes, hello?

676
00:31:37,629 --> 00:31:39,430
Hello, is this Hikaru?

677
00:31:39,931 --> 00:31:42,433
I got your number from Shunichiro.

678
00:31:42,500 --> 00:31:45,303
Yes, I'm with Sora now.

679
00:31:45,370 --> 00:31:47,138
She's a bit far away now.

680
00:31:47,205 --> 00:31:49,908
-Where are you?
<i>-At the hospital.</i>

681
00:31:51,075 --> 00:31:52,577
She's testing her blood type?

682
00:31:52,644 --> 00:31:55,580
<i>Yes, she wants to know her blood type.</i>

683
00:31:57,615 --> 00:31:58,917
Did you tell her?

684
00:31:59,417 --> 00:32:00,952
That Type O moms can't have AB kids.

685
00:32:01,019 --> 00:32:03,855
No, that's not exactly right.

686
00:32:04,822 --> 00:32:07,392
But when we were thinking of characters
for our manga,

687
00:32:07,458 --> 00:32:08,793
we started talking about it.

688
00:32:09,861 --> 00:32:11,896
I realized it was strange at first.

689
00:32:11,963 --> 00:32:14,032
Stop her from taking the test!

690
00:32:16,968 --> 00:32:18,036
How?

691
00:32:18,636 --> 00:32:20,838
You're right. How?

692
00:32:21,706 --> 00:32:23,875
<i>I think she will do the test.</i>

693
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:25,343
<i>Even if I stopped her.</i>

694
00:32:26,678 --> 00:32:29,314
Ms. Aoi, I'm with her.

695
00:32:30,581 --> 00:32:32,450
I might not be enough,

696
00:32:33,318 --> 00:32:35,920
<i>and I know I'm just a kid.</i>

697
00:32:36,888 --> 00:32:38,189
<i>But I'm with her.</i>

698
00:32:40,091 --> 00:32:42,660
-Oh, she's coming back.
<i>-Hikaru.</i>

699
00:32:43,962 --> 00:32:44,963
Please…

700
00:32:45,630 --> 00:32:47,131
Please look after Sora.

701
00:32:48,433 --> 00:32:49,267
Yes, ma'am.

702
00:32:51,402 --> 00:32:53,771
Who was that? Your girlfriend again?

703
00:32:53,838 --> 00:32:55,440
A new girlfriend?

704
00:32:55,506 --> 00:32:56,607
Something like that.

705
00:32:59,143 --> 00:33:00,778
I heard it's pretty common.

706
00:33:01,346 --> 00:33:02,347
What?

707
00:33:02,413 --> 00:33:03,948
People who mistakenly remember

708
00:33:04,015 --> 00:33:05,950
their own blood type.

709
00:33:06,551 --> 00:33:08,553
I see.

710
00:33:09,053 --> 00:33:11,522
Miss Minase. Miss Sora Minase?

711
00:33:12,023 --> 00:33:13,124
Yes!

712
00:33:30,808 --> 00:33:34,679
I have to go do prep for dinnertime.

713
00:33:47,291 --> 00:33:50,194
What should I do, Gon-chan?

714
00:33:50,695 --> 00:33:53,598
Sora's leaving me. She's going away.

715
00:33:54,766 --> 00:33:57,068
No way that would happen!

716
00:33:58,302 --> 00:34:00,872
I was lying this whole time.

717
00:34:00,938 --> 00:34:02,507
I kept it a secret.

718
00:34:02,573 --> 00:34:04,876
She'll never forgive me!

719
00:34:05,376 --> 00:34:08,279
What are you saying? It'll be okay.

720
00:34:11,949 --> 00:34:13,484
It's over.

721
00:34:15,386 --> 00:34:16,988
Everything's over.

722
00:34:19,157 --> 00:34:20,658
Stop saying that, alright?

723
00:34:21,526 --> 00:34:22,894
Nothing's ending.

724
00:34:32,203 --> 00:34:33,304
I was Type AB.

725
00:34:35,173 --> 00:34:36,007
TYPE AB+

726
00:34:36,074 --> 00:34:37,041
No doubt about it.

727
00:34:38,109 --> 00:34:39,310
I'm Type AB.

728
00:34:43,514 --> 00:34:44,348
Yeah.

729
00:34:54,192 --> 00:34:55,092
Thanks.

730
00:34:55,159 --> 00:34:57,095
-I'll pay you back.
-It's fine.

731
00:35:01,132 --> 00:35:03,267
Do you want to be left alone?

732
00:35:07,572 --> 00:35:08,840
Oh, are you busy?

733
00:35:08,906 --> 00:35:10,208
No.

734
00:35:10,274 --> 00:35:12,043
Not in the slightest.

735
00:35:12,944 --> 00:35:15,613
I made you come with me the whole day.

736
00:35:16,747 --> 00:35:18,783
I just finished
my temporary part-time job so…

737
00:35:22,019 --> 00:35:23,087
Where did you work?

738
00:35:25,356 --> 00:35:28,626
I made banana omelets at a bread factory.

739
00:35:29,193 --> 00:35:30,161
What is that?

740
00:35:30,661 --> 00:35:33,131
You don't know?
They sell it at convenience stores.

741
00:35:33,197 --> 00:35:34,799
They have a whole banana inside.

742
00:35:34,866 --> 00:35:36,601
I roll that up with cream and cake.

743
00:35:36,667 --> 00:35:37,902
That sounds good.

744
00:35:37,969 --> 00:35:40,037
I was peeling the bananas

745
00:35:40,104 --> 00:35:41,672
all day.

746
00:35:41,739 --> 00:35:44,242
-No way!
-It's true! From morning to night!

747
00:35:44,308 --> 00:35:46,544
It takes three or four times to peel
a banana, right?

748
00:35:46,611 --> 00:35:48,079
I can do it in one go!

749
00:35:48,146 --> 00:35:49,113
You're lying!

750
00:35:49,180 --> 00:35:51,616
It's true! There's a trick.

751
00:35:51,682 --> 00:35:53,351
Really?

752
00:36:01,792 --> 00:36:04,262
Hey, don't you have your date
with Doctor Wataru today?

753
00:36:05,029 --> 00:36:08,166
Yeah. It's at six today.

754
00:36:09,267 --> 00:36:10,434
On a day like this?

755
00:36:12,069 --> 00:36:13,638
I promised, so I have to go.

756
00:36:15,373 --> 00:36:18,242
I don't feel like going home,

757
00:36:18,876 --> 00:36:19,810
so it works out.

758
00:36:21,612 --> 00:36:22,513
I see.

759
00:36:25,082 --> 00:36:26,050
What time is it now?

760
00:36:27,285 --> 00:36:28,252
It's…

761
00:36:29,921 --> 00:36:31,222
It's 4:30.

762
00:36:32,356 --> 00:36:33,291
I see.

763
00:36:34,892 --> 00:36:36,227
I have more time.

764
00:36:38,796 --> 00:36:39,630
Yeah.

765
00:36:52,343 --> 00:36:53,978
Is that person a stranger?

766
00:36:56,414 --> 00:36:57,415
What?

767
00:36:58,449 --> 00:37:00,518
Because if we're not related by blood,

768
00:37:01,052 --> 00:37:02,520
we're strangers, right?

769
00:37:03,554 --> 00:37:06,190
Don't say it like that.

770
00:37:07,858 --> 00:37:09,527
Your mom would be sad.

771
00:37:13,564 --> 00:37:16,033
I don't know what went on with her, but…

772
00:37:18,436 --> 00:37:20,171
Do you have any ideas?

773
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:31,482
I don't know what went on with her, but,

774
00:37:33,317 --> 00:37:35,586
I'd probably thank her first.

775
00:37:37,288 --> 00:37:39,557
She wasn't related by blood,
but she raised you.

776
00:37:42,627 --> 00:37:43,995
Aoi Minase

777
00:37:45,129 --> 00:37:47,965
loves Sora Minase very much.

778
00:37:51,936 --> 00:37:53,404
That's how I see it.

779
00:37:59,944 --> 00:38:00,778
Minase…

780
00:38:02,513 --> 00:38:03,581
No…

781
00:38:04,081 --> 00:38:05,483
What should I do?

782
00:38:06,917 --> 00:38:08,919
I shouldn't have…

783
00:38:09,687 --> 00:38:12,990
I shouldn't have tested my blood type!

784
00:38:14,358 --> 00:38:17,128
-Minase…
-Why?

785
00:38:17,194 --> 00:38:19,363
Why did it become like this?

786
00:38:19,864 --> 00:38:22,533
-Minase.
-I love Mom a lot.

787
00:38:23,034 --> 00:38:26,771
-What's happening to me?
-Minase!

788
00:38:26,837 --> 00:38:29,907
Minase! Hold it together, alright?

789
00:38:31,375 --> 00:38:33,611
I'm here. It'll be okay.

790
00:38:34,111 --> 00:38:35,346
You're not alone.

791
00:38:37,415 --> 00:38:38,516
I'm not alone?

792
00:38:38,582 --> 00:38:40,718
Yeah. I'll be here. I won't go away.

793
00:38:41,419 --> 00:38:45,156
I can't say things like I'll protect you.
I won't.

794
00:38:45,222 --> 00:38:47,325
I can't be that cool,

795
00:38:47,858 --> 00:38:49,260
or be that confident,

796
00:38:50,061 --> 00:38:51,262
but I'll be here.

797
00:38:52,530 --> 00:38:53,798
No matter what happens.

798
00:38:55,366 --> 00:38:56,400
Don't forget I'm here,

799
00:38:57,468 --> 00:38:58,302
okay?

800
00:39:00,104 --> 00:39:01,772
Irino!

801
00:39:04,208 --> 00:39:05,042
Irino.

802
00:39:05,910 --> 00:39:08,446
<i>This was my first time being hugged</i>

803
00:39:08,512 --> 00:39:09,613
<i>by a boy.</i>

804
00:39:11,248 --> 00:39:13,884
<i>It was like a weak grandma</i>

805
00:39:13,951 --> 00:39:15,986
<i>leaning against an utility pole.</i>

806
00:39:17,254 --> 00:39:20,791
<i>Far from romantic, but sincere.</i>

807
00:39:22,259 --> 00:39:24,462
<i>Stay, Irino.</i>

808
00:39:25,596 --> 00:39:27,598
Honey!

809
00:39:28,833 --> 00:39:30,301
Chili pepper.

810
00:39:32,069 --> 00:39:33,237
Yuzu citrus.

811
00:39:36,907 --> 00:39:38,109
Alright!

812
00:39:40,478 --> 00:39:41,512
What!

813
00:39:42,146 --> 00:39:44,382
Is this Iberian pork bacon?

814
00:39:44,448 --> 00:39:47,084
You have such nice ingredients,
rich woman!

815
00:39:47,585 --> 00:39:49,820
Call me anytime you want.

816
00:39:52,490 --> 00:39:54,125
I'll answer within three rings.

817
00:39:59,897 --> 00:40:01,265
Yes, hello?

818
00:40:01,866 --> 00:40:04,368
You're right. That was one ring.

819
00:40:07,938 --> 00:40:10,875
Don't get cocky just because you're cute!

820
00:40:11,776 --> 00:40:12,610
Huh?

821
00:40:12,676 --> 00:40:14,578
No, I'll work hard

822
00:40:14,645 --> 00:40:16,947
so I can answer in half a ring

823
00:40:17,982 --> 00:40:19,049
next time round!

824
00:40:23,254 --> 00:40:26,090
Order up! Gon-chan's special soup.

825
00:40:26,657 --> 00:40:27,691
I don't want it.

826
00:40:27,758 --> 00:40:30,161
Don't say that! I made it for you.

827
00:40:50,214 --> 00:40:53,250
-So good!
-Right? The secret ingredient is miso.

828
00:40:53,951 --> 00:40:56,420
It's better to eat something.
You'll feel calmer.

829
00:40:56,921 --> 00:40:57,755
Yeah.

830
00:40:58,355 --> 00:41:00,724
Sora went on her date
with Doctor Wataru, right?

831
00:41:00,791 --> 00:41:04,195
Yeah. I got a call from Hikaru just now.

832
00:41:04,261 --> 00:41:06,263
Hikaru's a handsome boy,
and Doctor Wataru's

833
00:41:06,330 --> 00:41:08,432
a good doctor. Sora's so popular!

834
00:41:08,499 --> 00:41:11,802
A man on each arm.
Maybe she doesn't need you!

835
00:41:14,705 --> 00:41:17,341
Hey, it was just a joke.

836
00:41:17,408 --> 00:41:20,578
It just means Sora's grown up.
She'll understand.

837
00:41:21,445 --> 00:41:22,913
-You think so?
-Yeah.

838
00:41:24,248 --> 00:41:26,283
What will happen to us?

839
00:41:28,619 --> 00:41:29,787
Listen, Aoi.

840
00:41:31,589 --> 00:41:32,523
No matter what,

841
00:41:33,023 --> 00:41:35,626
I'll protect the both of you.

842
00:41:36,260 --> 00:41:38,095
I proposed to you and Sora here. Remember?

843
00:41:39,263 --> 00:41:40,331
What?

844
00:41:40,397 --> 00:41:42,099
Proposed? What do you mean?

845
00:41:44,235 --> 00:41:45,069
Hey, you.

846
00:41:46,003 --> 00:41:46,937
Hey.

847
00:41:49,740 --> 00:41:50,941
If you need help,

848
00:41:51,442 --> 00:41:54,745
I can raise her with you.

849
00:41:57,414 --> 00:41:58,883
Hey, it's alright!

850
00:42:00,184 --> 00:42:02,520
Nako helps me out too, so I'll be fine.

851
00:42:03,387 --> 00:42:05,623
What? That was a marriage proposal?

852
00:42:05,689 --> 00:42:07,691
I didn't get that at all!

853
00:42:07,758 --> 00:42:10,895
I thought you were just offering to
come help me again tomorrow.

854
00:42:10,961 --> 00:42:12,930
Back then, Sora cried so much at night.

855
00:42:12,997 --> 00:42:15,533
She wouldn't let me sleep.
I was tired and hazy.

856
00:42:15,599 --> 00:42:18,302
You have to explain to me,
"This is a marriage proposal!"

857
00:42:18,369 --> 00:42:20,638
Like I'd ever say, "Please marry me!"

858
00:42:20,704 --> 00:42:23,107
But you left the country
for years after that!

859
00:42:23,173 --> 00:42:24,642
To heal my broken heart.

860
00:42:24,708 --> 00:42:27,511
As if! You married Étoile immediately!

861
00:42:27,578 --> 00:42:28,679
That's irrelevant.

862
00:42:29,246 --> 00:42:31,248
-I decline your offer.
-What?

863
00:42:31,315 --> 00:42:33,984
I respectfully decline your proposal.

864
00:42:35,319 --> 00:42:37,855
I'm not proposing right now!
Just back then!

865
00:42:37,922 --> 00:42:39,924
I'd never propose to you ever again!

866
00:42:39,990 --> 00:42:42,126
I just felt bad for you back then.

867
00:42:42,192 --> 00:42:44,562
It was out of pity, okay?

868
00:42:45,195 --> 00:42:46,564
FRENCH BULLDOG

869
00:42:46,630 --> 00:42:47,665
Oh.

870
00:42:48,432 --> 00:42:52,036
I just noticed that you looked down today.

871
00:42:52,870 --> 00:42:53,904
I do?

872
00:42:54,872 --> 00:42:56,507
Did something happen?

873
00:43:00,010 --> 00:43:01,178
That's good.

874
00:43:02,446 --> 00:43:03,280
Oh.

875
00:43:04,014 --> 00:43:06,584
I might have a slight fever.

876
00:43:06,650 --> 00:43:07,952
What? In that case…

877
00:43:08,018 --> 00:43:10,154
No. I don't need a treatment today.

878
00:43:12,256 --> 00:43:13,390
I'm sorry.

879
00:43:14,391 --> 00:43:15,459
I'm going home.

880
00:43:27,071 --> 00:43:28,572
Yes!

881
00:43:28,639 --> 00:43:29,907
SORA MINASE

882
00:43:29,974 --> 00:43:31,108
Yeah.

883
00:43:31,775 --> 00:43:32,977
Yeah, what's up?

884
00:43:33,043 --> 00:43:34,745
<i>I don't want to go home.</i>

885
00:43:35,245 --> 00:43:37,014
Oh, makes sense.

886
00:43:37,748 --> 00:43:38,882
<i>Can I come over?</i>

887
00:43:39,516 --> 00:43:41,552
What? Now?

888
00:43:42,219 --> 00:43:44,855
Wait, my room right now…

889
00:43:44,922 --> 00:43:47,491
Is really messy…

890
00:43:47,558 --> 00:43:48,726
Where are you right now?

891
00:43:51,028 --> 00:43:53,530
-You find it okay?
-Yeah.

892
00:43:53,597 --> 00:43:56,233
-On Google Maps.
-Right. Come in.

893
00:43:57,001 --> 00:43:57,835
Thank you.

894
00:44:05,009 --> 00:44:07,478
-Hey, Miss Minase?
-Yeah?

895
00:44:07,544 --> 00:44:10,047
Don't do these things to random men.

896
00:44:10,114 --> 00:44:12,750
Certain men of a certain age might
want to do you.

897
00:44:12,816 --> 00:44:14,718
You're doing me?

898
00:44:15,285 --> 00:44:17,788
No! Not me, never!

899
00:44:17,855 --> 00:44:20,157
I'm not so desperate for girls
that I'd need you!

900
00:44:20,224 --> 00:44:21,058
But, you know,

901
00:44:21,925 --> 00:44:24,595
if you do this to random men,
you don't know what they'll think!

902
00:44:25,095 --> 00:44:25,996
I choose my men.

903
00:44:26,497 --> 00:44:28,732
I was chosen! No, that's irrelevant.

904
00:44:29,233 --> 00:44:31,001
I changed the sheets here.

905
00:44:31,068 --> 00:44:33,070
I have water and food in the fridge.

906
00:44:33,137 --> 00:44:34,238
Help yourself.

907
00:44:34,304 --> 00:44:35,539
What about you?

908
00:44:37,574 --> 00:44:39,743
Well, you know,

909
00:44:40,444 --> 00:44:42,646
I'm of a certain age too.

910
00:44:42,713 --> 00:44:44,348
I'll spend the night at a manga café.

911
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:48,419
It'll be fine! I'll answer your call
in three rings.

912
00:44:48,485 --> 00:44:49,586
I did just now, right?

913
00:44:49,653 --> 00:44:51,021
I jumped out of the shower.

914
00:44:51,088 --> 00:44:51,922
Oh, right.

915
00:44:52,623 --> 00:44:53,991
I'm going here.

916
00:44:54,058 --> 00:44:55,726
Manga Café "Sea Turtle."

917
00:44:56,293 --> 00:44:58,595
It's really close. I can come by
if anything happens.

918
00:44:59,630 --> 00:45:00,931
Did you contact your mom?

919
00:45:02,299 --> 00:45:03,133
Yeah.

920
00:45:03,734 --> 00:45:05,436
I told her
I'm going out all night with a friend.

921
00:45:06,937 --> 00:45:07,771
Okay.

922
00:45:26,490 --> 00:45:27,524
SORA: I'LL BE OUT ALL NIGHT.
KEEP THE CHAIN UNLOCKED FOR ME.

923
00:45:27,591 --> 00:45:28,425
AOI: GOT IT!

924
00:45:40,504 --> 00:45:42,005
Sora's favorite drink.

925
00:45:42,773 --> 00:45:44,108
The Limoncello.

926
00:45:45,242 --> 00:45:47,344
ROOM 53 WITH RECLINING SEAT

927
00:45:48,679 --> 00:45:50,180
-Excuse me?
-Yes?

928
00:45:50,247 --> 00:45:51,281
You have a guest.

929
00:45:51,782 --> 00:45:52,616
What?

930
00:45:57,521 --> 00:45:58,555
Why are you here?

931
00:45:58,622 --> 00:46:00,457
100 YEN

932
00:46:00,524 --> 00:46:01,458
No!

933
00:46:04,561 --> 00:46:06,063
I didn't want to be alone.

934
00:46:08,832 --> 00:46:10,200
So I followed you here.

935
00:46:11,869 --> 00:46:13,904
You're too unguarded all of a sudden.

936
00:46:13,971 --> 00:46:15,139
Because you drew Jadwiga.

937
00:46:16,573 --> 00:46:17,407
What?

938
00:46:17,941 --> 00:46:20,110
Materializing what's in someone's heart

939
00:46:20,611 --> 00:46:23,480
and turning it into a drawing is

940
00:46:23,981 --> 00:46:27,618
the same thing as opening our hearts
to each other, right?

941
00:46:29,720 --> 00:46:31,522
When did you think that?

942
00:46:32,956 --> 00:46:34,525
I just made it up now.

943
00:46:35,025 --> 00:46:36,927
Stop that.

944
00:46:36,994 --> 00:46:39,096
Don't play with my emotions like that!

945
00:46:40,998 --> 00:46:42,099
It's so strange.

946
00:46:45,435 --> 00:46:48,639
When I'm with you, my heart is free.

947
00:46:50,207 --> 00:46:51,875
I really want to cry.

948
00:46:52,609 --> 00:46:53,944
And I don't know what to do.

949
00:46:55,179 --> 00:46:57,848
But with you, I can find an escape route

950
00:46:58,715 --> 00:47:00,617
for my heart.

951
00:47:00,684 --> 00:47:02,119
I'm an escape route then?

952
00:47:02,186 --> 00:47:04,221
But beyond that escape route,

953
00:47:04,721 --> 00:47:05,689
I can see light.

954
00:47:06,190 --> 00:47:07,491
Because my name's Hikaru?

955
00:47:09,760 --> 00:47:11,328
Mom mentioned that.

956
00:47:12,362 --> 00:47:13,831
"You both have pretty names

957
00:47:13,897 --> 00:47:15,465
meaning light and sky,

958
00:47:16,233 --> 00:47:18,569
so why don't you call each other
by first names?"

959
00:47:21,371 --> 00:47:23,440
Whenever I call you Minase,

960
00:47:24,308 --> 00:47:25,809
I see the sky.

961
00:47:27,044 --> 00:47:28,912
I feel like a blue sky is

962
00:47:29,513 --> 00:47:30,814
opening up in front of me.

963
00:47:32,983 --> 00:47:34,484
Was that a joke?

964
00:47:34,551 --> 00:47:35,652
No, I'm serious.

965
00:47:39,122 --> 00:47:40,123
I'm tired.

966
00:47:41,458 --> 00:47:42,793
Today was a tiring day.

967
00:47:44,494 --> 00:47:45,629
I'm going to sleep.

968
00:47:52,936 --> 00:47:53,937
Hey…

969
00:47:55,172 --> 00:47:57,507
What do you mean, sleep?

970
00:48:01,545 --> 00:48:03,347
She's really asleep.

971
00:48:25,102 --> 00:48:26,236
Mom.

972
00:49:00,170 --> 00:49:01,972
Thank you. I'm fine here.

973
00:49:03,407 --> 00:49:04,775
Are you fine by yourself?

974
00:49:05,809 --> 00:49:06,743
Yeah.

975
00:49:08,312 --> 00:49:10,047
It's still three rings, right?

976
00:49:11,882 --> 00:49:14,584
Of course. Buy me dinner next time, okay?

977
00:49:15,218 --> 00:49:16,053
Yeah.

978
00:49:16,687 --> 00:49:18,956
<i>Yakisoba</i> at Odaya? <i>Taiyaki?</i>

979
00:49:21,625 --> 00:49:22,459
Oh.

980
00:49:23,393 --> 00:49:24,828
-Huh?
-There's a gachapon.

981
00:49:25,862 --> 00:49:26,997
CELLS AT WORK
THAT TIME I GOT REINCARNATED AS A SLIME

982
00:49:27,497 --> 00:49:28,865
Do they have White Blood Cell?

983
00:49:28,932 --> 00:49:30,867
Jadwiga will go in here one day!

984
00:49:30,934 --> 00:49:32,436
Good idea.

985
00:49:36,773 --> 00:49:38,075
The shiny glass ball.

986
00:49:38,875 --> 00:49:39,977
You're right.

987
00:49:40,644 --> 00:49:42,279
Your favorite.

988
00:49:42,980 --> 00:49:44,648
My favorite.

989
00:49:46,650 --> 00:49:47,718
If I get it, it's yours.

990
00:49:48,285 --> 00:49:49,119
What?

991
00:49:49,619 --> 00:49:52,622
This makes the city look upside down,
so it's interesting, right?

992
00:49:53,457 --> 00:49:56,460
If you want to cry, look at the world
through this.

993
00:49:57,361 --> 00:49:58,862
Will you get it, though?

994
00:49:58,929 --> 00:50:00,564
Of course I will!

995
00:50:04,668 --> 00:50:05,602
What?

996
00:50:08,872 --> 00:50:11,341
Wow!

997
00:50:20,050 --> 00:50:22,019
<i>This will be my lucky charm.</i>

998
00:50:23,120 --> 00:50:23,954
<i>Yeah!</i>

999
00:50:36,466 --> 00:50:37,401
I'm home.

1000
00:50:39,836 --> 00:50:42,472
I just woke up. I'm making coffee.

1001
00:50:42,973 --> 00:50:45,108
-Want some?
-Yeah.

1002
00:51:02,459 --> 00:51:03,393
Mom.

1003
00:51:04,127 --> 00:51:05,095
Yeah?

1004
00:51:07,230 --> 00:51:08,131
Am I

1005
00:51:08,965 --> 00:51:10,500
not your daughter?

1006
00:51:13,603 --> 00:51:15,872
PREVIEW OF NEXT EPISODE

1007
00:51:15,939 --> 00:51:17,441
<i>I found this in the forest.</i>

1008
00:51:17,507 --> 00:51:20,277
<i>-That's just like the novel.</i>
<i>-This is an umbilical cord, right?</i>

1009
00:51:20,343 --> 00:51:21,812
They might take away Sora…

1010
00:51:21,878 --> 00:51:23,780
Are bloodlines that important?

1011
00:51:23,847 --> 00:51:25,949
<i>I'm worried that Sora's going to break.</i>

1012
00:51:26,016 --> 00:51:28,485
Pushing a kid onto Mom, who's not family?
How irresponsible!

1013
00:51:28,552 --> 00:51:29,252
THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

1014
00:51:29,319 --> 00:51:30,887
Apologize to Suzu!

1015
00:51:30,954 --> 00:51:31,788
Subtitle translation by: Yukimi Ohashi

